On September 29, 2018, the President signed into law two bills: H.R. 6897, the "Airport and Airway Extension Act of 2018, Part II," and S. 3479, the "Department of Veterans Affairs Expiring Authorities Act of 2018." H.R. 6897 extends authorization for Federal Aviation Administration programs and related revenue authorities until October 7, 2018. S. 3479 extends certain expiring authorities affecting veterans and their families, including healthcare, benefits, homelessness, and other authorities. It also includes amendments to various authorities related to healthcare and other matters.